 If you had these folks to tank.. who'd you choose?</span><hr size=1> The entire concept of a main tank is to NEVER lose agro. It is not a good idea to intentionally plan to shift agro since the fact is, you cant be sure you will get it back, nor can you be sure that the person it shifted to (wizard or cleric) will be able to handle the damage and wont lose an important cast.<br>
<br>
I agree a rogue can tank, but I wouldnt want one in my group as main tank IF the intent was to shift agro to get in a couple backstabs. That would be as bad as the Ranger using jolt while playing main tank, or the Monk feigning as main Tank.<br>
<br>
The entire purpose of main tank is to get and KEEP agro for the entire fight. If you plan to ping/pong it around, you dont need a main tank. And your cleric better be ready to cast heal on everyone even in a single mob encounter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 604<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/3/02 12:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ranger or monk</span><hr size=1> Bards and rogues can't tank compared to those two, not at high levels.  Prefer the ranger to do the main tank thing, so the monk can pull and the rogue can BS.  Also, at upper levels, really only rangers and SKs can hold agro over a monk.<br>
